I've probably thought of 30 different ways to spontaneously kill myself or others along the walk from dorm row to lobby 7. It's interesting, and sparks my imagination in the mornings.

#11148 The year is 6006. The world has collapsed since all available computing power has been allocated to posting the 6.006 Fall 2017 final grades. The world's top scientists have estimated that the grades will be available on WebSIS shortly after the heat death of the Universe.

There was once hope that the onset of quantum computing would hasten the process, but all researchers have died in the meantime. A small group of survivors clings on to hope and makes a yearly pilgrimage to the ruins of MIT to check the last computer not being used to post grades. This year they check Piazza.

"Will there be final regrades?"

'No'
